# Jordan chat history

_Saved preferences and decisions from chats (not a full Cursor transcript)._

Jordan is **not** an engineer; replies to him should use **clear, plain English** when explaining tools or limits.

## How new agents pick this up

- Instructions **load automatically** when this project is opened in Cursor. Read **`00-agent-start-here.mdc`** for the full bundle order.

## What actually sticks (plain English — Jordan asked “plugin or auto-save?”)

**There is no secret plugin that downloads your whole Cursor chat history into Git.** Assistants inside Evair‑H5 read **whatever is committed in this repo** (rules + this file).

| What helps | Does it reduce repeat mistakes? |
|------------|----------------------------------|
| **This file (`jordan-chat-history.mdc`) + other `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files** | **Yes.** New agents for **Evair‑H5** receive them automatically when Cursor injects **`alwaysApply`** rules. Tell an assistant plainly what must never regress; **they are supposed to add a bullet here** during the session (Jordan does **not** need a cue phrase). |
| **`scripts/save.sh`** after edits | **Yes for teamwork + Netlify.** It **commits and pushes Git** — that is **not** the same button as “save chat”, but **without push** nobody else (and sometimes not even you tomorrow) gets the latest written rules. |
| **Cursor → Settings → Rules for AI** | **Yes, globally** — short lines that apply to **every** project you open. |
| **Cursor “Memories”** (if your Cursor version shows it) | **A little** — good for short facts; **not** a copy of every chat. |
| **“Old chats” inside Cursor** | Assistants **cannot** auto-import them into this folder. If something matters, it must land as **text in a file** (above). |

**Bottom line:** Memory you can rely on = **written in project files**. Auto-save assistants use = **`save.sh`** when Git should update. Plugins don’t replace that.

---


## HARD LIMIT — full Cursor chat replay

- Cursor keeps past **threads inside the product**, not in Git. Agents **cannot** silently download Jordan’s entire chat history into a fresh session.
- This file is therefore the **writable memory** Jordan controls through normal work—with **agents doing the clerical updating** so he doesn’t memorize cue phrases.

---

## Agents DEFAULT — proactively save what Jordan cares about (Jordan should not rely on cue phrases)

**Jordan does **not** have to say things like “add this to Jordan chat history.”** Whenever he communicates something that reads as **lasting** — do this in **the same work session**:

1. **Append a concise bullet** under the best matching heading below — or create a dated line under **`### Auto-captured (rolling)`**.
2. **Merge duplicates** instead of stacking near-identical bullets; trim older wording if superseded.
3. **Run `scripts/save.sh`** when you touched this repo (same turn as substantive work), unless Jordan asked for purely local experimentation.

Treat as candidates for persistence when Jordan clearly means **policy**, not trivia:

- “Always / never / don’t regress / you keep messing up…”
- UX, copy, or workflow choices he wants unchanged next time  
- Tone (e.g. English-only replies to Jordan) or deploy rhythm  
- Frustrations after **repeated mistakes** — capture the corrective rule explicitly

**Do not log:** small talk, one-off hypotheticals, ephemeral experiments he labels temporary.

If a new bullet would **contradict** `.cursor/rules/product-decisions.mdc` or other locked rules — **tell Jordan politely**, don’t bury a conflict here.

Jordan **may still** explicitly ask “save this”; that’s optional, not required.

Other files stay authoritative:

- `.cursor/rules/ongoing-work.mdc` — current work thread  
- `.cursor/rules/product-decisions.mdc` — locked product decisions (e.g. AI assistant tone, no emojis)  
- `.cursor/rules/agent-quality.mdc` — logic, regressions, pushback  

## Communication

- Prefer **English** when the assistant replies **to Jordan** (avoid switching assistant explanations into Chinese unless he asks).

## Edits Jordan made — approval before changing

- After **Jordan** changes files himself (manual edits in Cursor, copy, wording, spacing, wiring, etc.), assistants must **not** overwrite, revert, or rework those edits **unless Jordan explicitly approves in chat** — or his message clearly asks you to revise that exact work (same thread).
- If the next assistant step would touch the same lines or contradict Jordan’s version, **stop**, spell out the mismatch in plain English, and **ask how he wants to proceed** before using tools to edit.
- Applies to fixes and tidy-ups too: treating Jordan’s version as provisional until he says go prevents surprise rollbacks.

## Deploy and live previews

- After meaningful changes in **this repo**, finish with **`bash scripts/save.sh "short message"`** in the **same session** when Jordan wants GitHub updated. That push is what triggers **Netlify** (there is no separate "push only to Netlify"). Expect ~1–3 minutes build time after GitHub receives the commit.

See also: `.cursor/rules/auto-save-workflow.mdc`.

## OPEN APP / mobile gate (marketing — do not regress)

- OPEN APP QR modal (**`MobileOnlyNotice`**) — **shared ack** **`evair_desktop_signin_acked.v4`**:
  - **Marketing OPEN APP** (hybrid): **`min-width: 768px`** → show QR unless acked. **`max-width: 767px`** → handheld session (**`isMobileUserAgentClient()`** or **`(pointer: coarse)`** + **`(hover: none)`**) skips straight to **`/app`**. Narrow desktop windows still get QR on OPEN APP tap.
  - **`/app` shell**: desktop browsers **auto-open the same QR** on load when **`isAppPath()`**, viewport **`≥768px`**, **`(hover: hover)`** + **`(pointer: fine)`**, not native WebView, not **`#app-preview`**. Native app + real phones stay uninterrupted.
  For other marketing CTAs, **`isMobileDevice()`** stays separate; do not conflate.

- **"Continue on desktop anyway"**: persist ack (**`v4`**); **stay on current URL** — no fake navigation. Subsequent **`/app`** visits and OPEN APP taps respect ack until cleared.

Relevant implementation: `hooks/useMobileSignInGate.ts`, `components/marketing/MobileOnlyNotice.tsx`, `utils/device.ts`.

